1. Introduction

ST-T1024 is the first deterministic AI inference architecture designed for embedded and edge hardware. This guide provides a practical, step-by-step approach to programming ST-T1024 on a given microcontroller (MCU) or microprocessor (MPU) — be it ARM, RISC-V, or other architectures.

The core insight: ST-T1024 eliminates floating-point multipliers, stochastic sampling, and massive DRAM arrays — dramatically reducing the complexity of silicon and firmware implementation. This simplicity makes it accessible for any medium-skilled embedded engineer to implement.

Key ST-T1024 Metrics:

Metric Value
Energy per query 3.7 µJ
Latency (AET) 680–800 ns
Memory footprint 0.7 MB (75% ROM / 25% SRAM)
Arithmetic Ternary {-1, 0, +1} — XNOR + popcount
Power gating 99.9% off-time, <5 ns wake

