2. Architecture Overview for MCU Implementers

Before writing code, understand the 6-step deterministic pipeline you will implement:

Step Component Function
1 Intent Harvesting Capture and normalize input query
2 FIS Triage Fuzzy Inference System — route to correct domain tile
3 FSM Scheduling Finite State Machine — enforce WCET/AET timing
4 Tile Activation Power-on only the relevant domain tile
5 Execution Ternary Tiny Transformer inference
6 0V Power-Down Immediate power-gating to idle state

The FSM cycle counter is hardware-enforced — it halts execution if the tile exceeds its time budget, guaranteeing Assured Execution Time (AET).

