5. ARM-Specific Implementation Notes

5.1 Cortex-M7 (STM32H7, i.MX RT1024)

Advantages:

· High performance (up to 480 MHz)
· Double-precision FPU (optional — not required for ST-T1024)
· MPU for memory protection
· DSP instructions (can accelerate ternary ops)

Key Configuration:

```c
// Enable CPU cache for deterministic access
SCB_EnableICache();
SCB_EnableDCache();

// Configure MPU to protect ROM (immutable) and SRAM
MPU_Region_Init(MPU_REGION_ROM, ROM_BASE, MPU_SIZE_2MB, 
                MPU_AP_READ_ONLY, MPU_REGION_ENABLE);
MPU_Region_Init(MPU_REGION_SRAM, SRAM_BASE, MPU_SIZE_512KB,
                MPU_AP_READ_WRITE, MPU_REGION_ENABLE);
```

5.2 Cortex-M4 / M33

· Lower power consumption
· Sufficient for ST-T1024 at reduced clock speeds
· Ensure FPU is disabled to save energy (ternary ops don't need it)

