6. RISC-V-Specific Implementation Notes

6.1 NEORV32

Advantages:

· Open-source, sovereign
· Customizable — add ternary engine as custom instruction
· 16 fast interrupts for deterministic response

Custom Instruction for Ternary XNOR:

```assembly
# Custom RISC-V instruction: TERNARY_XNOR rd, rs1, rs2
# Performs XNOR on ternary vectors in rs1 and rs2
# Result stored in rd

# In C: use intrinsic
inline ternary_t ternary_xnor_insn(ternary_t a, ternary_t b) {
    register ternary_t result;
    __asm__ volatile (
        ".insn r 0x0B, 0x0, 0x0, %0, %1, %2"
        : "=r"(result)
        : "r"(a), "r"(b)
    );
    return result;
}
```

